PrecisAppointment of Earle McCurdy, of St. John's, Newfoundland, as a Canadian representative to the General Council of the Northwest Atlantic Fisheries Organization to hold office during pleasure for a term of two years; and as a Canadian representative to the Fisheries Commission of the Northwest Atlantic Fisheries Organization to hold office during pleasure for a term of two years; in the place of Raymond Alfred Andrews.
